# Domain Layer Rules

## Purpose

Pure business logic with ZERO framework dependencies.

## Allowed Imports

- Other `src/domain/` modules
- Standard library only (no npm packages except utility types if absolutely needed)

## Forbidden Imports

- `chrome.*`
- `react`, `react-dom`
- `dexie`, `idb`
- `fetch`, `XMLHttpRequest`
- DOM APIs (`document`, `window`)

## Entity Rules

- Entities have identity (`id` field) and lifecycle methods
- Use factory functions or static `create()` methods for construction
- Validate invariants in constructor/factory (throw `DomainError`)
- Entities are mutable only through explicit methods (e.g., `lead.changeStage()`)

```typescript
// ✅ Good
class Lead {
  changeStage(newStage: LeadStage): void {
    if (!isValidTransition(this.stage, newStage)) {
      throw new DomainError(`Invalid transition: ${this.stage} → ${newStage}`);
    }
    this.stage = newStage;
    this.updatedAt = Date.now();
  }
}

// ❌ Bad — direct property mutation from outside
lead.stage = 'won';
```

## Value Object Rules

- Immutable (readonly properties)
- Equality by value, not reference
- Self-validating in constructor

```typescript
// ✅ Good
class PhoneNumber {
  readonly value: string;
  constructor(raw: string) {
    const normalized = normalizeE164(raw);
    if (!isValidE164(normalized)) throw new DomainError('Invalid phone');
    this.value = normalized;
  }
  equals(other: PhoneNumber): boolean {
    return this.value === other.value;
  }
}
```

## Repository Interfaces

- Define in `src/domain/repositories/`
- Return domain entities, never raw DB rows
- Use case-specific query methods, not generic CRUD

```typescript
interface ILeadRepository {
  findById(id: string): Promise<Lead | null>;
  findByPhone(phone: PhoneNumber): Promise<Lead | null>;
  findByStage(stage: LeadStage): Promise<Lead[]>;
  save(lead: Lead): Promise<void>;
  delete(id: string): Promise<void>;
}
```

## Service Interfaces

- Define in `src/domain/services/`
- One interface per capability (Interface Segregation)

```typescript
interface IMessageSender {
  send(chatId: string, text: string): Promise<SendResult>;
}

interface IMessageReader {
  getRecentMessages(chatId: string, limit: number): Promise<ConversationMessage[]>;
}
```

## Agent Interfaces

- Each agent owns ONE decision surface
- Return typed handoff contracts with confidence + rationale

```typescript
interface AgentHandoff<T> {
  contractVersion: '1.0';
  agentId: string;
  confidence: number;
  rationale: string;
  payload: T;
  provenance: 'user' | 'prospect' | 'system';
}
```

## Error Handling

- Use `DomainError` class for business rule violations
- Never catch and swallow in domain — let application layer handle
